text: The Contulmo ground frog (Eupsophus contulmoensis) is a frog. It lives in Chile. ==Home== People find this frog under logs and rocks in forests with Nothofagus plants. Scientists saw this frog between 50 and 740 meters above sea level. Scientists have seen this frog in one protected place: Contulmo National Monument. ==Young== The adult female frog lays eggs in holes. ==Danger== Scientists from the IUCN say this frog is in danger of dying out. People change the places where the frog lives to make tree farms for pine and eucalyptus trees. Fires and too many visitors to the frog's home can also cause problems. ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Eupsophus contulmoensis
